  "body": "Hi. When using pipelines in Sci-Kit a lot of times Transformations are used. For example X is scaled with a Standardscaler\r\nand Y ist transformed with a log function to get a normal distribution.\r\n\r\nWould it be possible to implement a parameter in the shap plots, that when I use a model which is trained with a scaled training set,\r\nI can use the Inverse of the used Scaler to Transform the plot annotations back to the original values. Or even a function to define which columns/features I want to transform back for the annotations.\r\n\r\nThis would make it a lot more intuitive to interpret features from the real world, for example if you have the feature Age with the real range of values 0-90 instead of some obscure scaler betwen -3.010 and 2.6984 .",
